 The effect of Hyperimmune Bovine Colostrum on NASH Regulatory T cells (Tregs) are recognized as an important immunomodulatory component of the adaptive immune system.

 Immune dysregulation may lead to chronic inflammation, triggering chronic insulin insensitivity and non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH).

 The role of Tregs in the adipose tissue in the regulation of NASH was not previously studied.

 Aim: To assess the effects of Tregs stimulation on hepatic injury and insulin resistance in NASH.

